✅ Purpose

Used to access internal services (like RDP/SMB/HTTP) through a compromised machine (pivot host).

🧠 Concept

You map:

Your local port → Internal target port via pivot
⚙️ Command

ssh -L 33389:192.168.1.10:3389 user@10.10.10.5 -N

🔍 Line-by-Line Explanation
ssh → Start SSH client
-L → Local port forwarding option
33389 → Local port on YOUR machine (listener)
192.168.1.10:3389 → Internal target (RDP service)
user@10.10.10.5 → Pivot host (already compromised)
-N → No shell, only tunnel (keeps connection clean)
🎯 Access Service

xfreerdp /v:127.0.0.1:33389 /u:admin /p:pass /cert:ignore

127.0.0.1:33389 → Redirected to internal machine
You are now accessing internal RDP via pivot
